1> [quote]Ashenbone drakes can be mezzed by lower spells as well :-) The trick is to cast the mezz in melee range (like with all dragons)[/quote]<br>
<br>
This is good information but a little inaccurate - not &quot;all dragons&quot; are belly casters. In fact I would have to say that the majority of dragons are not belly casters.<br>
<br>
The easiest way to tell is if you are up against a belly caster is if every spell you cast is totally resisted regardless of your relative level to the dragon then it is most likely a belly caster - meaning to land a spell you must be so close you are practically under it's belly.<br>
<br>
I would advise you to not run under every dragon's belly with impunity however since some dragons have massive proximity aggro. It's all a case of &quot;die and learn&quot; in the world of EQ. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=illuminataa>Illuminataa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Enchanter Realm Member</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#330000>(9/9/03 12:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=272.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: level of creature you can mez?</span><hr size=1> Greater Fetter has a -30 MR adjust while Bliss only has a -10 MR adjust.<br>
<br>
I used to have a lot of trouble handling multiple adds in BoT, especially if one of them was a Krieger, with their insane MR.<br>
<br>
One day, i decided to try rooting mobs before trying to mez them since mez w/o tash bounced so often anyways and tashing first is like saying &quot;BEAT ME TO DEATH PLEASE!&quot;.<br>
<br>
What i found is that root might bounce a few times before landing, but with -30 MR on it has a better chance of landing w/o a tash than does a mez w/o tash.<br>
<br>
Once rooted, i am free to tash and mez and voila!, mob in control way faster than if mez bounces a few times and i am having to kite the mob around trying to land tash and mez while getting the stuffing beat out of me.<br>
<br>
I have been using this technique a lot and find that i get mobs under control much faster on the average and w/o having the cleric blow a lot of mana keeping me alive.. or rezing me.<br>
<br>
So what if the mobs hit a tank a few times while they are rooted! The tanks are much better equipped to withstand the beating than i am and it saves cleric mana and the effort of a TMer trying to save me.<br>
<br>
Root + Tash + Mez... try it, you'll like it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
